FBIS3-53035 "drnes007_r_94005" FBIS-NES-94-007 Document Type:Daily Report 11 Jan 1994 India Government Totals 1993 Foreign Investment BK0901165494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 9 Jan 94 BK0901165494 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Foreign direct investment has crossed 1600 crore rupees last year. An official release in New Delhi says this reflects the increasing response to the new industrial policy and the economic reforms. The investment inflows were a meagre 350 crores rupees during 1991. The year end review of the industrial scene shows that the infrastructure sector has achieved a near six percent growth rate. The release says the government has approved 37 projects proposed under the centrally sponsored scheme of growth centers.
